<Font|headerFont>TEAM DISPLAY<Font|helpFont><p><p>

The Team display provides information on your teammates as well as available information that has
been discovered about your opponents during the course of the game. The only way to access
Command view for every sector is from a station, so the Team display is a great way to find out
the locations of all your teammates while flying.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>To toggle the expanded or mini Team display<Font|helpFont><p><p>

<Bullet|hlpbullet|Press F6 or SHIFT+F6.><p><p>

<Bullet|hlpblank|The expand/collapse arrow in the upper-right corner of the Team display
toggles the size of your Team display between expanded and mini. The mini Team display offers
a simple drop-down menu at the top to select which team you would like to see team statistics
on.><p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Selected Team --<Font|helpFont>Shows the name of the currently selected
team. When the expanded Team display first appears, your team will be highlighted. To select
another team to view, simply click it.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Pilot Callsign --<Font|helpFont>Shows the name
of the pilot. The owner of the game (lightning icon) and the team leader
(crown icon) of each team are also indicated.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Kills --<Font|helpFont>Shows how many kills the
pilot has made in the game so far.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Deaths --<Font|helpFont>Shows how many times the
pilot has died.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Sector --<Font|helpFont>Shows the current sector
location of the pilot.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Ship --<Font|helpFont>Shows what the pilot is
currently manning. A ship icon means the pilot is in a ship. A turret icon
means he is in a turret on a ship. The eye icon means he is in
Command view. A shovel icon indicates a miner.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Wing --<Font|helpFont>Shows the wing the pilot belongs to. You can change
wings by selecting your player name, clicking and holding
<Font|smallBoldFont>Change Wing,<Font|helpFont> and then selecting the
wing you want to join.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Credits --<Font|helpFont>Shows the amount of money the pilot currently has.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Objective --<Font|helpFont>Shows the command that a
pilot has accepted.<p><p>

Along the bottom of the Team display are additional buttons that provide
you with further team interaction.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Team Deposit/Stop Donating --<Font|helpFont>Makes
continuous deposits of all your money to whomever you select, usually your
team leader or investor.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Single Deposit --<Font|helpFont>Makes a single
deposit of 100 credits to whomever you select.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Take Me To --<Font|helpFont>Transports you, via
Command view, to the selected player or computer-controlled ship, such as a constructor or
miner. This will also work with any enemy teams you have encountered. If an enemy player is
currently being observed by anyone on your team, even your probes, you can be
taken directly to their position by selecting their name and then
clicking <Font|smallBoldFont>Take Me To.<Font|helpFont><p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Change Wing --<Font|helpFont>Lets you join or
change your current wing. You can change wings by selecting your player name, clicking and holding
<Font|smallBoldFont>Change Wing<Font|helpFont>, and then selecting the
wing you want to join. Different wings offer their own communications
channel in chat mode.<p><p>

The team leader also has an additional button.<p><p>

<Font|smallBoldFont>Boot Pilot --<Font|helpFont>As team leader, you can
boot a player from your team. Select the player you want to eject from the
game, and then click <Font|smallBoldFont>Boot Pilot.<Font|helpFont>
